        "resolution": "Adopt Kobe's recommendation: use Redis sorted sets (ZADD/ZREMRANGEBYSCORE/ZCARD) for a true sliding window. This correctly implements Bird's rolling window requirement. MJ's key pattern is replaced with rate_limit:{api_key} as a single sorted set per key."
      },
      {
        "conflict": "Pippen specified Retry-After as 'TTL of the current window key', which assumed MJ's fixed-window design with per-window TTLs.",
        "resolution": "With sorted sets, Retry-After is computed as: 60 - (now - timestamp_of_oldest_entry_in_set). This gives the exact number of seconds until a slot opens in the rolling window."
      }
    ],
    "open_questions": []
  },
